overview: In 2012, a man named Jeffrey Roberts miraculously realized his dream of having his own talk show. Not Quite Late Night with Jeffrey Roberts, as it was called, only lasted for a couple episodes, however, and is canceled within weeks of its debut. In a story of failure and showbiz, the enthusiastic documentary filmmaker, Giorgio Quizno, explores the mythology of this flash-in-the-pan show.
title: Not Quite Late Night
